	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New Orleans</placeName> <date>Sept 15<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1858</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
				<p>From every part of the <placeName>U States</placeName> Donations<lb/> are daily recd by our Various Benevolent<lb/> Institutions to assist their <sic>releiving</sic><lb/> the sick &#38; Indigent while religious<lb/> Institutions are also in receipt of<lb/> Various Sums to defray the Expense<lb/> of Burying the Dead  These Donations<lb/> come from Christians to Christians<lb/> one House &#40;<sic>Jewellers</sic>&#41; or our City<lb/> I forget the name &#40;a Handsome white<lb/> marble Front Store on <placeName>Chestnut St</placeName>&#41;<lb/> sent our Howard Association &#36;500.00<lb/> I need not tell you How exhausted<lb/> any Treasury becomes when the<lb/> drain is constant for doctors<lb/> nurses medicines &#38;c.  Our President<lb/> of the Gent Hebr. Ben Association<lb/> <persName>L B Cain Esq</persName> has worked hard &#38;<lb/> Business Health &#38;c is neglected<lb/> by him in his constant Labour<lb/> of seeing to the sick.  Our congregation<lb/> <placeName>Rampart Sr.</placeName> has <sic>allready</sic> Buried<lb/> about 50 all Charity &#38; of course</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>a very Heavy outlay for their exhausted<lb/> Treasury&#44; our &#8220;Home&#8221; must take<lb/> in a large number of orphans<lb/> left Destitute Oh its a sad scene<lb/> to witness &#38; I will not call up<lb/> the better feelings of your nature by<lb/> recounting all the misery<lb/> we witness here our Jewish<lb/> people of both sexes work<lb/> hard &#38; faithful &#38; are many<lb/> of them completely worn out&#33;<lb/>  The Fever still continues its<lb/> fatal work carrying off whole<lb/> &#38; frequently portions of a family.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Its to be hoped our <sic>Bretheren</sic><lb/> of your own admission Cities will<lb/> not wait a similar call to one<lb/> we made &#40;&#38; I am happy to acknow<lb/>ledge not in vain&#41; once before<lb/> but some Influential good Philantro<lb/><sic>phists</sic> will be found to go to work &#38;<lb/> send some relief ere its too late<lb/> Excuse this hasty scrawl yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">ever Truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Isaac Hart</persName></p>
				<p><persName>Mr DeSilva</persName> paid me &#36;25.00 for the Hebrew Prayer Books &#40;11&#41;</p>
		</body>
